        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 11 at 5:46PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 545 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Tanner, or near Athens, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Decatur, Madison, Athens, Hartselle, Redstone Arsenal, Priceville,
Triana, Huntsville International Airport, Tanner, and Somerville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
